SIMPLE: spitter
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spitter
<hw>Spit"ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Spit</er> to
eject from the mouth.]</ety> <def>One who ejects saliva from the
mouth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spitter</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Spitter
<hw>Spit"ter</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Spit</er> an iron
prong.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who puts meat on a spit.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A young deer whose antlers begin
to shoot or become sharp; a brocket, or pricket.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spittle</ent>⟦br⟧
